Bayesian approach
here is a simple bayesian model to generate the same inference:
\[
\begin{align}
y &\sim \text{Bernoulli}(p)\\
\text{logit}(p) &= \alpha + X\beta\\
\alpha &\sim \text{Normal}(-2.5, .5)\\
\beta &\sim \text{Normal}(0, .5)\\
\end{align}
\]
normally we would go through a careful process of checking our priors here. At this time we won’t because the point here is to show how the bayesian posterior includes uncertainty, not to demonstrate a full Bayes workflow.
First we compile the model, then we’ll look at the Stan code:

library(cmdstanr)

